<TEXT>
charges were filed tuesday against 41 
alleged mobsters including the son of jailed mafia boss little 
nicky scarfo in a statewide sweep that authorities said signals 
the end of the scarfo era 
also charged was reputed decavalcante crime boss john riggi and 
alleged members of the brunoscarfo gambino colombo luchese 
genovese and decavalcante organized crime families 
twentynine of the defendants were arrested by tuesday evening 
authorities said they were arraigned before superior court judge 
michael degnan in essex county 
the charges listed in the criminal complaint will be presented 
to a state grand jury 
more than 150 state police fanned out across new jersey early 
tuesday to make the arrests which came after a yearlong 
investigation based on information from george fresolone a member 
of the brunoscarfo family police said 
fresolone who is now in hiding secretly recorded more than 400 
conversations with alleged mobsters and also recorded the 
initiation ritual of five members into the mob authorities said 
officials refused to release details about fresolone why he 
became an informant or whether he was being protected by police 
but they said his tapes revealed how the mafia families 
cooperated with each other and shared illicit profits 
although nicodemo scarfo sr known as little nicky is 
serving a 69year federal sentence on murder and extortion charges 
authorities claim he ran a criminal empire from prison in illinois 
via his son nicodemo scarfo jr 25 
the scarfo organization is in a state of disarray said col 
justin dintino a spokesman for the state police its been 
greatly weakened by previous indictments arrests and killings 
within the organization 
if the individuals arrested today are convicted i believe 
that the final nail in the scarfo organized crime organization has 
been placed he said 
besides riggi and scarfo jr among those apprehended were 
anthony tony buck piccolo 67 of collingswood and joseph 
scoops licata 48 of florham park allegedly top advisers to 
the elder scarfo 
riggi was released on 100000 bail tuesday but scarfo jr 
piccolo and licata remained in the essex county jail bail was set 
at 100000 each for scarfo and piccolo and 150000 for licati 
piccolo and licata were charged with racketeering and leading 
organized crime 
licata who also was charged with illegal gambling and theft by 
extortion operated loansharking bookmaking and extortion 
activities from the east side social club in newark the criminal 
complaint alleged 
riggi 65 of elizabeth was charged with similar offenses as 
well as witness tampering bribery and hindering apprehension and 
scarfo jr of scotch plains was charged with promoting gambling 
and racketeering 
the other defendants were charged with various offenses 
including conspiracy racketeering and drug distribution 
riggi was convicted last month of extortion and violating 
federal labor laws and faces up to 65 years in prison 
john mavilla 43 a member of the newark zoning board was 
charged with bribery and official misconduct he is accused of 
taking a 2000 bribe from an allegedly mobcontrolled hauling 
company to approve a use variance 
fresolone taperecorded conversations from august 1989 until 
late this summer when he was initiated into the brunoscarfo crime 
family according to a 90page police affidavit 
during the ceremony the trigger finger of each initiate was 
pricked each man said may i burn in hell if i betray my friends 
in the family as he crumpled a piece of burning paper with his 
bare hands the affidavit said 
a gun and a knife symbolized that members live by the gun and 
die by the gun live by the knife and die by the knife it said 
