a guy i just got off the phone with admitted that he only had 
10 pounds 19 he worked in kuwait his house is in kuwait and 
his bank account is there he has no way of getting money she 
said 
these people arent professionals they are not wealthy 
expats expatriots many are oil and gas workers with only the 
clothes they stand up in 
trained volunteers have said relatives and escapees are calling 
in a serious state of desperation 
many cant talk about it without crying both women and men i 
get emotional ms copley said her voice faltering 
the foreign office also set up a telephone line for relatives 
but it was heavily criticized for making it a paypercall number 
the foreign office subsequently announced that the proceeds would 
go to charity 
ms copley said she would not criticize the foreign office but 
she added families are not interested in future charities they 
have immediate problems 
