<TEXT>
after a threemonth delay to fix a 
hydrogen leak space shuttle columbia will lift off on an astronomy 
mission sept 1 nasa says 
nasa on monday set the launch date for the nine to 10day 
mission liftoff is scheduled for 117 am edt 
columbia will carry seven astronauts including four astronomers 
who will operate the 150 million astro observatory from the 
shuttles cargo bay in their study of ultraviolet light and xrays 
from stars supernovas and other celestial bodies 
the mission has been on hold since the fuel leak was found in 
may a similar problem with atlantis prompted the space agency in 
june to ground the shuttle fleet temporarily 
columbias flight will be the first shuttle mission since april 
when discovery carried the flawed hubble space telescope into 
orbit it also will be the first shuttle flight in five years 
devoted entirely to scientific research 
