<TEXT>
scores of arabs have fled kuwait into 
saudi arabia by walking across the desert or slipping past iraqi 
soldiers by car but now only a few western refugees are making the 
run 
three britons who made it across the border on sunday were the 
last reported western escapees along that route border area 
residents said monday 
one saudi resident speaking in a telephone interview said 
fewer kuwaiti families were arriving but that dozens of egyptians 
pakistanis and indian workers were walking part of an 80mile 
stretch to reach saudi arabia 
the ones coming in just look very confused said the 
resident who could see the refugees at the saudi arabian border 
checkpoint at khafji 
the ones who go on foot seem to just move through the dense 
iraqi troop movements on the other side he said speaking on 
condition of anonymity but the cars do not seem to be coming 
across now as they used to do in earlier days 
some travelers said iraqi troops and tanks were apparently 
cutting off open border areas which hundreds of westerners and 
kuwaitis have fled across since iraqi president saddam hussein 
ordered his troops into kuwait on aug 2 
attempting a border crossing can be a deadly maneuver refugees 
said 
they shoot at any approaching car said a traveler who 
arrived in khafji late last week the soldiers fired at a car 
behind me and injured a 37yearold woman in her right thigh 
life inside iraqioccupied kuwait is also growing more dangerous 
iraqi television which is now broadcast in kuwait announced 
last week that anyone hoarding food would be executed 
one traveler told the khafji residents that the sultan center a 
large grocery store in the kuwait city suburb of salmiya was 
completely out of provisions 
but kuwaitis say their families usually have large quantities of 
food stored usually sufficient for a month 
