disheveled and dejected their eyes bloodshot 
they huddle around transistor radio listening to reports from 
free kuwait radio that are broadcast clandestinely somewhere in the 
persian gulf 
their newspapers among the liveliest in the arab world despite 
a censorship clamped since 1986 are beginning to emerge in other 
capitals alqabas in london alanbaa in cairo and shortly 
