delta enterprise corp wants consumers to 
remove and discard plastic labels and decals from its delta luv 
popcorn baby walker because they pose a choking hazard 
the walkers have been associated with five incidents of choking 
the consumer product safety commission said monday all occurred 
when children pulled off the decals on plastic toy dials on the 
walker trays and placed them in their mouths 
the six colorful round decals which measure about 1 inches in 
diameter should be removed immediately if they can be easily 
dislodged the commission said labels that are firmly stuck should 
be checked periodically and removed if they become loose the 
commission said 
adults should also remove the plasticcoated delta luv label 
with surrounding stripes found on the front of the tray although 
no complaints have been received about these labels the commission 
said 
the paper warning label located under the tray should not be 
removed 
approximately 100000 of the walkers have been sold nationwide 
since 1984 
