faction under prince johnson which controls most of monrovia 
announced a truce 
johnson has pledged to hold monrovias port for the arrival of 
the african force which doe also has welcomed 
soldiers loyal to the two men told a diplomat who ventured into 
the streets of monrovia on monday that they were prepared to join 
forces to resist any attack by taylors men 
they said they welcomed the west african intervention and would 
not fire on the task force 
taylor has the largest army in the country around 10000 men 
but most are illtrained peasant recruits and young boys for 
weeks does soldiers have kept them at bay 4 miles east of the 
clifftop presidential mansion 
johnsons and does men have fended off several attacks from 
taylor who last week launched a lastditch bid to oust doe and 
capture the port before the west africans arrive 
the war began with a dec 24 invasion from the northeastern 
border with ivory coast by 200 rebels who accused doe of 
corruption and tribalism 
thousands of civilians joined their ranks seeking vengeance 
against government soldiers who were unable to hold back the rebels 
and instead killed thousands of peasants johnson split with taylor 
in february to form a rival faction 
monrovia has been besieged by the three armies since the end of 
june when water supplies electricity and telephone communications 
were cut 
those who have not fled or been evacuated have been without 
fresh food supplies for weeks in the city where bodies rot in the 
streets and no hospitals are operating 
