<TEXT>
following is the text of iraqi president 
saddam husseins message to president bush carried by the official 
iraqi news agency in arabic and translated by the associated press 
once again us president george bush stood before the 
american people to twist words hide facts or part of the facts 
and confuse causes with results 
in his speech yesterday 20th of august 1990 before american 
war veterans he referred to the americans in iraq and stressed on 
calling them hostages despite iraqi declarations that clarified 
beyond any doubt that the americans are here as result of a real 
aggression launched against the arab nation and iraq by president 
bush himself and his ally british prime minister margaret 
thatcher 
had this aggression not occurred had president bush 
considered realistically the interests of the american people then 
none of what happened to the americans and others would have 
happened nevertheless what happened to them remains the lightest 
all the formulas that such circumstances require even by the 
stands of america itself 
president bush know or should know that america itself and 
during world war ii had interned tens of thousands of its citizens 
simply because they were of japanese origin and based this action 
on the theory of deterring larger harm by lesser or smaller harm 
so if this precedent already exists and is recorded in the 
files of the united states of america along with other actions 
recorded in the files on humanity isnt it a form of racial 
discrimination when what is allowed for other nations including 
the americans is not allowed for the arabs including the iraqis 
despite all this the iraqis have stated clearly that what has 
happened was a force majeure dictated by the circumstances among 
many other options 
and we regret what happened 
preventing some foreigners from traveling is not an act of 
vengeance but a force majeure to deter a crime of aggression 
president bush intends to commit against the people of iraq after 
the crime he committed in occupying the shrine of kaaba mecca and 
the tomb of the prophet medina and should he proceed to commit 
this crime then a major catastrophe will befall not only this 
region but the entire world 
bush continues in his speech to talk about the outlaws 
comparing clearly between iraq and its representatives and hitler 
forgetting that all these descriptions apply to him because iraq 
did not send its fleets and aircraft to attack europe or america 
it is bush and those whom he dragged with him to the cliff who were 
the ones who embarked the aircraft and ships and invaded our 
region after desecrating our sanctities they want to kill the 
people and rob them of their human rights 
is there any doubt that these descriptions apply to presient 
bush when he is seeking to fuel a war that might burn the entire 
world is there a better proof of his intentions after he 
stonewalled all the initiatives and solutions which we had offered 
for settling the main problem or the issue of the foreigners which 
is a result of the main problem 
it is undoubtedly misbehavior a reflection of poor insight 
and wisdom for the white house to reject our initiative of the 
12th of august 1990 a few hours after it was aired before 
president bush took it upon himself to request official text to 
guard against inaccuracy in translation or deficiency in phrases 
for technical reasons 
is this possible president of the united states of america 
he who does not want history to link him to the basic 
characteristics of hitler must search thoroughly for peaceful 
means and not rush into preparations for war 
what we presented in our initiative of the 12th of august 
1990 and in our letter to the families of the foreigners whom the 
national council decided to host is a clear way for anyone to 
distance himself from the basic descriptions of hitler 
characteristics of love and peace that are desired by the 
peoples of the world 
at the same time we defend without fear from any arrogant 
and sinful tyrant or aggressor the principles of our religion and 
holy shrines and the honor of the homeland and nation even all the 
values of humanity combined 
the claim that the american forces have come here to defend 
saudi arabia does not stand in the face of the conflicting fact 
because the reality is that we have no intention of attacking saudi 
arabia or any other country 
however to say that your forces came here to defend american 
interests you know that the arabs including iraq are not opposed 
to legitimate interests whether they be the wests in general or 
the united states 
you also know that prosperity scientific and technical 
development and the promotion and flourishing of growth cannot be 
achieved in the way the arabs want it to without the wests 
cooperation 
to achieve this the arabs have to sell oil the major oil 
market is europe and the united states in addition to japan 
i assume that president bush knows that iraq for example 
sold a third of its oil to the united states until the 2nd of 
august 1990 and that iraq was against the feverish price increases 
that took place in 1973 we have documents to prove that 
at any rate the arabs including iraq wish to sell their oil 
for all the purposes we have already mentioned not to drink it or 
freeze it 
the fact that iraq owns about 20 percent of the worlds oil 
reserves does not annul the principles we have already referred to 
if whoever owns oil is boycotted by the world it would be all 
the more reason for the world to boycott america and the saudi 
arabian government 
after all is not food more vital to the human being than oil 
we answer by saying yes by all human standards it is more 
vital than oil the human being cannot survive without food 
if president bushs criteria for boycotts hostility war and 
siege are applicable to iraq merely because it will or that it 
already does own 20 percent of the worlds oil reserves then it 
is all the more reason that these standards in every sense be 
applied to those who own the same percentage or more of food 
primarily grain 
then what is required is that the world stand against america 
and australia 
but if us interests have become so small and narrow in 
bushs view that they are restricted to the relations between bush 
and saudi king fahd before bushs assumption of the presidency 
and followed his election and if their interests have become so 
narrow that they do not consider them as they should in terms of 
good and positive relations with a large and great nation but 
consider them only with jaber alahmed the croesus of kuwait and 
his band who is unable to construct a useful sentence and who 
along with people like him has been a source of shame to the arabs 
and proof to the west of their backwardness then you will be 
cursed by what you are doing 
before concluding my letter i would like to say that the 
source of potential and power mr bush does not lie in the size 
of armies and technological superiority nor in your alliance with 
those who betrayed their nation and people it lies in the 
inclination toward what is right 
however god is greater and more powerful than everyone and 
as we have previously said america would not have been a 
superpower if it had not been influential in the world 
in order to remain influential it must respect the freedom of 
peoples and the right of nations to make their own choices it also 
must respect other peoples sanctities and feeling 
if you continue to ignore this then i warn of the 
consequences and i hereby record for history that pursuing this 
policy will cause america to fall from its present status and it 
will lose many opportunities 
in all circumstances if your pursue war and blockade you 
will be defeated and with the help of god we will triumph 
god is great shame be on the shameless 
saddam hussein on the 30th of moharram 1411 corresponding to 
21st of auugust 1990 
</TEXT>
