when the two germanys finally unite 
they will be a mighty nation of 78 million people stretching from 
france to poland 
the two germanys were founded in 1949 their division resulted 
from adolf hitlers defeat in 1945 east germany was run by 
stalinist leaders for four decades while west germany immediately 
adopted a parliamentary democracy system of government 
west germans built a prosperous nation from the ashes of world 
war ii west germany has one of the worlds most powerful economies 
and is known for its excellence in hightechnology its currency 
the deutsche mark is king in europe 
over the past two years west germany has also established itself 
as an important player in world politics 
east germany was long considered one of the most prosperous 
nations in eastern europe but last falls revolution revealed a 
nation that had been weakened by years of communist mismanagement 
and corruption 
east germany has major industries including chemical 
production but many of its industries are on the verge of 
collapse overburdened by antiquated production practices 
crumbling factories and skyrocketing debts 
financial experts say the germans will expand their economic 
might after unification 
but many problems will have to be overcome such as soaring 
unemployment in what is now east germany 
some experts predict that within 10 years east germans will 
enjoy the same kind of prosperity as their western neighbors 
when the two nations unite their total area will be roughly the 
size of montana 
