pan am said monday it has had to cancel a small number of 
flights and put smaller planes on others but spokesman jeff 
kriendler said the impact has been minimal 
northwest airlines spokesman bob gibbons would not rule out the 
possibility of future disruptions but said that as of monday 
afternoon there had been no disruptions in the carriers regular 
passenger flights 
a lot depends on when they call for the airplanes he said 
tim neale air transport association spokesman said most 
airlines have a minimal number of planes in reserve and the 
military callup could reduce their options in case mechanical 
failure takes an airliner out of service 
cargo carriers are in a relatively slow season now neale said 
but could feel the pinch if the emergency fleet is still being used 
during the christmas season 
further forced usage of commercial jets would require an order 
from the defense secretary who could commandeer up to 506 
airliners for use on 48 hours notice 
this is the first time the civil reserve air fleet has been used 
since it was set up in 1952 during a period of bombshelter 
building and heightened concern over military readiness 
the initial order came from the military transportation command 
at scott air force base in illinois and requires planes to be used 
on military flights on 24 hours notice 
the planes remain available for commercial flights when they are 
not being used by the military 
carriers are paid for all flights under military contracts which 
require them to commit set numbers of aircraft and crews in times 
of crisis 
the airlines maintain operational control of their airplanes 
we just make them a deal they cant refuse said airlift command 
spokesman lt col mike cox 
airlines are paid for the mandatory military charters at rates 
set under their regular military contracts which include 
reimbursement for extra insurance costs and the cost of keeping the 
planes ready for such a callup 
the commitment to join the fleet is part of their obligation 
under lucrative military contracts that are a significant source of 
revenue for some airlines during peacetime 
cox said 20 or more dc10 dc8 l1011 and boeing 747 jetliners 
were being used each day since the fleet was activated 
the order to activate the civilian fleet came one day after 
transportation secretary samuel skinner had told authorities he 
thought it would be unnecessary transportation department 
officials said skinner was not involved in the military decision 
the military said it had tried for several days to conduct the 
massive airlift by calling upon airlines individually to charter 
planes but found it couldnt muster enough planes for the rapid 
troop deployment 
</TEXT>
