the month company spokesman ray cox said 
more closings are possible after the effects of the step are 
analyzed he said monday 
about 1600 employees in 21 states will be affected but 95 
percent of them will be moved to other stores cox said most of 
the stores are concentrated in texas california georgia and 
florida 
he would not say how much the closings were expected to save or 
how much it would cost to terminate the leases 
analysts said they doubted that 200 closings would suffice to 
pull the company from the protection of us bankruptcy court 
where it filed for chapter 11 protection from creditors may 15 
the company determined which stores to close mainly by gross 
sales and profitability figures cox said but other factors 
including traffic counts and neighborhood deterioration also were 
taken into account 
