the burden of third world nations 
officials said more than 90 percent of a total 400 creditor 
banks have chosen from a list of five debtcutting options offered 
by venezuela 
the most popular options were the exchange of venezuelan debt 
for lowinterest 30year usguaranteed bonds and the loaning of 
fresh funds to venezuela 
least popular was the option that venezuela had pushed the 
hardest allowing venezuela to buy back debt on the secondary 
market at about 41 percent of its value 
