chrysler corp has renamed its arcad 
inc subsidiary created as a 5050 joint venture with the french 
automaker renault as jj international automotive corp the us 
company said tuesday 
the new name reflects the jj codename of a small 
sportutility vehicle the company wants to make and market there 
have been rumors that chrysler may decide to build the vehicle by 
itself or may be looking for a partner to replace renault 
in june chrysler said it terminated its 500 million agreement 
with renault because it was no longer economically attractive 
chrysler bought renaults stake in arcad for an undisclosed sum 
when the joint venture ended the us automaker said it would 
continue development on the small sportutility vehicle 
there has been speculation that chrysler will build the jj at 
its toledo ohio jeep plant as a kit with major assemblies such 
as body panels interiors and powertrains being made by suppliers 
that would cut chryslers investment in the vehicle 
the jj will be designed to compete with the daihatsu rocky 
suzuki sidekick and geo tracker 
